div.p:
That when the peoples good ſtands on the poſſeſſors ſide, then clearly he begins to gain right and power. That when the people think themſelves


   well, they manifeſtly conſent to the preſent Government.pag. 154. Beſides (ſaith he) who can aſſure they ſhall be beter by the return of the diſpoſſeſſed party▪ Surely by common preſumption the gainer is like to defend them better then he who loſt it. 
He comes ſo far as to conclude; That if the old Magiſtrate offer to return, he muſt be repulſed by force of Arms. His reaſoning is this;
